{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T04:05:53.828Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "ROC-AUC"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (Receiver Operating Characteristic - Area Under Curve) is a powerful evaluation metric for "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "binary classification models"}, {"type": "text", "text": " that measures how well a model can distinguish between positive and negative classes across "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "all possible classification thresholds"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — it's threshold-invariant and provides a single number summarizing overall model performance."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What It Is: Two Components"}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "ROC-AUC — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "ROC Curve"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (Receiver Operating Characteristic)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Visual representation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " of model performance across all thresholds:"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "How it's drawn"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Calculate "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "True Positive Rate (TPR)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "False Positive Rate (FPR)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " at every possible threshold\n- Graph "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "TPR (y-axis)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " vs. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "FPR (x-axis)"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- Each point = model performance at one threshold"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Axes"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "X-axis"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": False Positive Rate (FPR) = proportion of negatives classified as positive\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Y-axis"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": True Positive Rate (TPR) = proportion of positives correctly identified (also called "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Recall"}, {"type": "text", "text": " or "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Sensitivity"}, {"type": "text", "text": ")"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formulas"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n$$\\text{TPR (Sensitivity/Recall)} = \\frac{TP}{TP + FN}$$"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\text{FPR} = \\frac{FP}{FP + TN} = 1 - \\text{Specificity}"}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "[docs.tealium](https://docs.tealium.com/predict/evaluate-models/the-roc-auc-curve/)"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "AUC"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (Area Under Curve)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Single number"}, {"type": "text", "text": " that quantifies the area under the ROC curve:"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Meaning"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "\"AUC represents the probability that the model, if given a randomly chosen positive and negative example, will rank the positive higher than the negative.\""}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Interpretation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "AUC = 1.0"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Perfect classifier (100% probability of ranking positive > negative)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "AUC = 0.5"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Random guessing (no better than chance)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "AUC < 0.5"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Worse than random (predictions reversed)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "AUC > 0.5"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Better than random (useful model)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key insight"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": AUC is "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "threshold-invariant"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — it doesn't depend on the specific probability threshold used."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Visual: ROC Curve Interpretation"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "ROC Curve:\nTPR (Recall)\n  ↑\n1.0  ●                    ← Perfect model (top-left corner)\n     | \\\n     |  \\\n     |   \\\n     |    \\\n     |     \\\n0.5  |      ●───────────── ← Random guessing (diagonal line)\n     |\n0.0  ●────────────────────→ FPR\n     0.0                  1.0\n     \nGood model: Curve bends toward top-left\nAUC = Area under the curve (higher = better)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Perfect model"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": ROC curve reaches top-left corner → sensitivity = 1, specificity = 1\n"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Random model"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Diagonal line from (0,0) to (1,1) → AUC = 0.5"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How to Calculate AUC"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Process"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n1. Iterate over all cutoff probabilities between 0 and 1\n2. Calculate TPR and FPR at each cutoff\n3. Plot curve: FPR vs. TPR\n4. Calculate area under that curve = AUC"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Python implementation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from sklearn.metrics import roc_auc_score\n\n# Correct: Use predicted probabilities (not binary predictions)\nAUC = roc_auc_score(y_true, y_pred_prob)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key point"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Use predicted probabilities/y_pred_prob, not binary y_pred."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why ROC-AUC is Powerful"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Advantage"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Explanation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Threshold-invariant"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Evaluates across all thresholds, not just one"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Balanced comparison"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Good for comparing models regardless of threshold choice"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Single metric"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "One number summarizes overall performance"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Class imbalance"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Works well with imbalanced datasets"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Model ranking"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Measures probability model ranks positive > negative"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tabl